  "time_ut": 1658470977,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dda \u0db1\u0dc0 \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0daf\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dde\u0db4\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db8\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Draupadi Murmu is the new President of India",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "With the aim of electing the 15th president, the Indian presidential election was held on the 18th, and the results were released last night (21st).",
        "A woman managed to achieve a magnificent and historic victory in the presidential election. She is Draupadi Murmu, 64 years old.",
        "Draupadi Murmu is a woman representing the tribal community of the Indian state of Odisha.",
        "Accordingly, this is the first time that a woman representing the tribal community of India won the presidency. Draupadi Murmu will be sworn in as the new president on the 25th.",
        "According to the Constitution of India, the President of the country is elected not by popular vote, but by parliamentary vote. The central government of India is divided into two parts namely Lok Sabha (House of Representatives) and Raj Sabha (Upper House).",
        "The President is elected by the votes of the members of the Lok Sabha and the Raj Sabha and the representatives of the state councils.",
        "The role of the President of India is very important. The President is the formative leader of the Indian Executive, Legislature and Judiciary.",
        "The tenure of the President of India is 5 years. Draupadi Murmu contested the presidential election representing Prime Minister Narendra Modi's Bharatiya Janata Party-led National Democratic Alliance. Murmu's opponent was the 84-year-old Yashwant Sinha, who ran for the presidential election representing the opposition political groups led by the United Progressive Alliance. This is the second time that a woman has won the presidency of India.",
        "Pratibha Patil was the first woman to become the President of India. She was the 12th President of India and her tenure was from 2007 to 2012. Pratibha Patil is a member of the Indian Congress Party; A lawyer.",
        "Draupadi Murmu is a BJP member and she is also a teacher. She also served as the Governor of Jharkhand from 2015 to 2021. With the victory confirmed, Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi met Draupadi Murmu and congratulated her.",
        "A vote will also be held in Parliament for the post of Vice President of India. That is next August. This year, Jagdeep Dankar from the ruling party alliance and Margaret Alva from the opposition alliance are going to run for the post of vice president."
      ],
